<h5> <span class="mw-headline" id="For_Piano_solo_.28Montgomery.29">For Piano solo (Montgomery)</span></h5>

<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="General_Information">General Information</span></h2>
<div class="wi_body" style="width:100%">
<table border="0">

<tr>
<th class="wi_head">Work Title
</th>
<td class="wi_head" style="width:100%">Messiah
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th class="wi_head">Alt<span class="mh555">ernative</span><span class="ms555">.</span> Title
</th>
<td class="wi_head">
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Composer
</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Category:Handel,_George_Frideric" title="Category:Handel, George Frideric">Handel, George Frideric</a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th><span class="mh555">Opus/Catalogue Number</span><span class="ms555">Op./Cat. No.</span>
</th>
<td>HWV 56
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th><span class="mh555">I-Catalogue Number</span><span class="ms555">I-Cat. No.</span>
</th>
<td>IGH 265
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th><span class="mh555">Movements/Sections</span><span class="ms555">Mov'ts/Sec's</span>
</th>
<td>3 parts:
<h5> <span class="mw-headline" id="Part_I">Part I</span></h5>
<ul><li>Scene 1: <i>Isaiah's Prophecy of Salvation</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>1. Sinfony (instrumental)
</dd><dd>2. Comfort ye my people (tenor)
</dd><dd>3. Ev'ry valley shall be exalted (tenor)
</dd><dd>4. And the glory of the Lord (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 2: <i>The Coming Judgment</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>5. Thus saith the Lord of hosts (bass)
</dd><dd>6. But who may abide the day of His coming (alto or bass)
</dd><dd>7. And he shall purify the sons of Levi (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 3: <i>The Prophecy of Christ's Birth</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>8. Behold, a virgin shall conceive (alto)
</dd><dd>9. O thou that tellest good tidings to Zion (alto and chorus)
</dd><dd>10. For behold, darkness shall cover the earth (bass)
</dd><dd>11. The people that walked in darkness have seen a great light (bass)
</dd><dd>12. For unto us a child is born (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 4: <i>The Annunciation to the Shepherds</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>13. Pifa ("pastoral symphony": instrumental)
</dd><dd>14a. There were shepherds abiding in the fields (soprano)
</dd><dd>14b. And lo, the angel of the Lord (soprano)
</dd><dd>15. And the angel said unto them (soprano)
</dd><dd>16. And suddenly there was with the angel (soprano)
</dd><dd>17. Glory to God in the highest (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 5: <i>Christ's Healing and Redemption</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>18. Rejoice greatly, O daughter of Zion (soprano)
</dd><dd>19. Then shall the eyes of the blind be opened (soprano)
</dd><dd>20. He shall feed his flock like a shepherd (alto and soprano)
</dd><dd>21. His yoke is easy (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<h5> <span class="mw-headline" id="Part_II">Part II</span></h5>
<ul><li>Scene 1: <i>Christ's Passion</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>22. Behold the Lamb of God (chorus)
</dd><dd>23. He was despised and rejected of men (alto)
</dd><dd>24. Surely he has borne our griefs and carried our sorrows (chorus)
</dd><dd>25. And with his stripes we are healed (chorus)
</dd><dd>26. All we like sheep have gone astray (chorus)
</dd><dd>27. All they that see him laugh him to scorn (tenor)
</dd><dd>28. He trusted in God that he would deliver him (chorus)
</dd><dd>29. Thy rebuke hath broken his heart (tenor or soprano)
</dd><dd>30. Behold and see if there be any sorrow (tenor or soprano)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 2: <i>Christ's Death and Resurrection</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>31. He was cut off (tenor or soprano)
</dd><dd>32. But thou didst not leave his soul in hell (tenor or soprano)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 3: <i>Christ's Ascension</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>33. Lift up your heads, O ye gates (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 4: <i>Christ's Reception in Heaven</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>34. Unto which of the angels (tenor)
</dd><dd>35. Let all the angels of God worship Him (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 5: <i>The Beginnings of Gospel Preaching</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>36. Thou art gone up on high (soprano)
</dd><dd>37. The Lord gave the word (chorus)
</dd><dd>38. How beautiful are the feet (soprano)
</dd><dd>39. Their sound is gone out (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 6: <i>The World's Rejection of the Gospel</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>40. Why do the nations so furiously rage together (bass)
</dd><dd>41. Let us break their bonds asunder (chorus)
</dd><dd>42. He that dwelleth in heaven (tenor)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 7: God's Ultimate Victory
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>43. Thou shalt break them with a rod of iron (tenor)
</dd><dd>44. Hallelujah (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<h5> <span class="mw-headline" id="Part_III">Part III</span></h5>
<ul><li>Scene 1: <i>The Promise of Eternal Life</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>45. I know that my Redeemer liveth (soprano)
</dd><dd>46. Since by man came death (chorus)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 2: <i>The Day of Judgment</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>47. Behold, I tell you a mystery (bass)
</dd><dd>48. The trumpet shall sound (bass)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 3: <i>The Final Conquest of Sin</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>49. Then shall be brought to pass (alto)
</dd><dd>50. O death, where is thy sting (alto and tenor)
</dd><dd>51. But thanks be to God (chorus)
</dd><dd>52. If God be for us, who can be against us (soprano)
</dd></dl>
<ul><li>Scene 4: <i>The Acclamation of the Messiah</i>
</li></ul>
<dl><dd>53. Worthy is the Lamb (chorus)
<dl><dd>Amen (chorus)
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th><span class="mh555">Year/Date of Composition</span><span class="ms555">Y/D of Comp.</span>
</th>
<td>1741-09-14 (end date)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>First Perf<span class="mh555">ormance</span><span class="ms555">.</span>
</th>
<td>1742-04-13 in Dublin. New Music Hall, Fishamble Street
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Librettist
</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Category:Jennens,_Charles" title="Category:Jennens, Charles">Charles Jennens</a> (1700-1773)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Language
</th>
<td>English
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th><span class="mh555">Composer Time Period</span><span class="ms555">Comp. Period</span>
</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Category:Baroque" title="Category:Baroque">Baroque</a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Piece Style
</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Category:Baroque_style" title="Category:Baroque style">Baroque</a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>Instrumentation
</th>
<td>voices, chorus, orchestra <div class="expandline" style="background-color:#E8E8E8;margin-left:0;margin-top:0;padding:0">
<dl><dd><i>Solo Voices</i>
<dl><dd>2 sopranos, alto, tenor, bass
</dd></dl>
</dd><dd><i>Mixed Chorus</i> (SATB)<br /><i>Orchestra</i>
<dl><dd>2 (or 4) oboes, [bassoons], 2 (or 4) trumpets<br />timpani, strings, continuo (harpsichord and/or organ) </div>
</dd></dl>
</dd></dl>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<th>External Links
</th>
